<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-354-802  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 354 802.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  April 9 1990 v4 n14 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOD asks for more latitude in purchasing. (Department of Defense)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Department of Defense (DOD) proposes that Congress let thePentagon make significant changes to its acquisition system.andP;  TheDOD wants to test new procurement practices unconstrained byexisting laws, employ commercial buying practices when buyingcommercial products, and award more sole-source contracts.andP;  TheDOD also wants more flexibility in managing anticipated cuts incivilian and military personnel.andP;  These legislative reformsfulfill recommendations in the Jul 1989 'Defense ManagementReport' and have been greeted by industry analysis and lobbyistswith reactions ranging from disbelief to cautious approval ofcertain provisions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Government AgencyAcquisition SystemsPersonnel ManagementGovernment RegulationUnited States. Department of Defense.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>